values:
Apparently after that traumatic-wating-for-the-cab&nbsp;incident i decided to stay in the dorms during weekends and have an unlimited ''Me time'' of my own. But&nbsp;on Thursday evening&nbsp;just as I was about to take a nap (thank god I didn't), Ms Jenifah called me. 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ''Najiha, do you wanna go out with us?''&nbsp; 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;''Erm. When's that?''&nbsp; 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ''Errr. in 10 minutes?'' 
And so Khalisa (&nbsp;her eldest daughter) drove us (me, Ms Jenifah &amp; one of her students) to Dubai Festival City where we had supper and watched ''Taken''. Awesome movie on human trafficking. This is the kind of show that makes mums go ''AHAH! This is WHY I worry when you don't call!'' &amp; so&nbsp;on&nbsp;so forth.&nbsp;hawhaw. 

While we were having supper we got into an interesting conversation/gossiping (hehheh) pertaining to guys (generally), the arab culture annnd the students in AUS. It turns out that we can never run away from AUS students cos every minute there will surely be students saying hi to ms Jenifah. hmm i guess at least I felt kinda ''popular'' for&nbsp;the day-.-.
